Oh,and ... ARGH !
So you pass that nice structure 
struct input_event {
	struct timeval time;
	__u16 type;
	__u16 code;
	__s32 value;
};
to userland via read() ... cool, a structure that is not compatible
between 32 and 64 bits passed around via a read call. that will be fun
to fix.
